cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.HC 

This paper is about developing a methodology to address the interpretability of neural approaches in conversational scenarios. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also discusses the performances of different architectures, which falls under cs.LG (Learning). The use of synthetic data and dialogue self-play can be considered as a form of data augmentation, which falls under cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper also discusses the usability of conversational agents, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
